#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.pad:11
msgid ""
"Number of values padded to the edges of each axis. ``((before_1, "
"after_1), ... (before_N, after_N))`` unique pad widths for each axis. "
"``(before, after)`` or ``((before, after),)`` yields same before and after "
"pad for each axis. ``(pad,)`` or ``int`` is a shortcut for before = after = "
"pad width for all axes. If a ``dict``, each key is an axis and its "
"corresponding value is an ``int`` or ``int`` pair describing the padding "
"``(before, after)`` or ``pad`` width for that axis."
msgstr ""

